Process called "darwin_arm64_SYS_PROCESS_POLICY" returns Integer:
    Return 323
End Process

@Reasoning
Darwin has no `sched_getaffinity` syscall. The Linux interface (syscall 204
on x86_64 / 123 on arm64) returns the CPU affinity mask for a thread or
process. Darwin's threading model is built on Mach scheduling primitives
that do not expose hard CPU pinning to user space — instead it offers
"affinity hints" via `thread_policy_set(THREAD_AFFINITY_POLICY)` (a Mach
trap, NOT a BSD syscall) and CPU-count queries via `host_processor_info`
(another Mach trap) or `sysctlbyname("hw.activecpu")` (BSD syscall 274).
Returning -1 here is the canonical "not supported" sentinel; the
dispatcher's high-level wrapper for affinity queries must route to
`thread_policy_set` for hint-setting or to `sysctlbyname` to enumerate
available CPUs. We deliberately do NOT alias to 274 (sysctlbyname) because
its argument contract (mib name buffer, len, oldp, oldlenp, newp, newlen)
differs entirely from `sched_getaffinity(pid, cpusetsize, mask)` and
silent substitution would corrupt callers.
Source: XNU osfmk/kern/thread_policy.c; Apple Concurrency Programming
Guide "Thread Affinity"; man 3 sysctlbyname.
@End Reasoning

