Note:
============================================================================
GENERIC SYSCALL WRAPPERS
============================================================================
Darwin ARM64 syscall convention:
- X16 = syscall number (DIFFERENT from Linux which uses X8!)
- X0-X7 = arguments 1-8
- Stack = arguments 9+ (16-byte aligned)
- Return value in X0
:End Note

Process called "darwin_arm64_syscall_0" takes syscall_number as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Darwin ARM64 syscall with 0 arguments
    Applies BSD syscall class mask (0x2000000) for macOS compatibility
    :End Note
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        # Load syscall number into X16 (Darwin uses X16, not X8!)
        ldr x16, [fp, #-8]

        # Apply BSD syscall class mask (0x2000000)
        orr x16, x16, #0x2000000

        # Execute syscall (Darwin uses svc #0x80 for BSD syscalls)
        svc #0x80

        # Store result from X0
        str x0, [fp, #-16]
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "darwin_arm64_syscall_1" takes syscall_number as Integer, arg1 as Integer returns Integer:
