Process called "darwin_arm64_O_APPEND" returns Integer:
    Return 8
End Process

@Reasoning
POSIX file mode constants are identical across Darwin, Linux, and the BSDs
because they predate any platform-specific divergence — they are part of
the original Bell Labs UNIX permission encoding. MODE_0644 (rw-r--r--) is
the canonical default for regular files created via `open(O_CREAT)` or
`creat`; MODE_0755 (rwxr-xr-x) is the canonical default for executables
and directories created via `mkdir`. The numeric values 420 and 493 are
the decimal encodings of octal 0644 and 0755 respectively, computed as
(6 * 64) + (4 * 8) + 4 = 420 and (7 * 64) + (5 * 8) + 5 = 493.
Source: POSIX.1-2017 §sys/stat.h; XNU bsd/sys/stat.h.
@End Reasoning

Process called "darwin_arm64_MODE_0644" returns Integer:
    Return 420  Note: 0o644 = rw-r--r-- (regular file default)
End Process

Process called "darwin_arm64_MODE_0755" returns Integer:
    Return 493  Note: 0o755 = rwxr-xr-x (executable / directory default)
End Process

